section.section:
In determining the period of extension of a protective order under subparagraph (i) of this paragraph, the judge shall consider the following factors:
the nature and severity of the subsequent act of abuse;
the history and severity of abuse in the relationship between the respondent and any person eligible for relief named in the protective order;
the pendency and type of criminal charges against the respondent; and
the nature and extent of the injury or risk of injury caused by the respondent.
